2025-01-29 18:12 ET - News Release
Mr. Matthew Wilcox reports
ROBEX ANNOUNCES SPROTT LENDING AS DEBT PROVIDER FOR KINIERO GOLD PROJECT
Further to the announcement regarding advanced discussions on a debt facility during the fall, Robex Resources Inc. has mandated Sprott Resource Lending (U.S. Manager) Corp. as mandated lead arranger to provide a senior debt facility of up to $105-million (U.S.), with the option to increase it to up to $130-million (U.S.), which will be used to finance the construction of the Kiniero gold project in Guinea. Sprott has completed detailed technical, environmental and social due diligence on the project, and has received the approval from its investment committee to progress with the financing, subject to satisfactory completion and execution of all necessary legal documentation, lodgment of security documents, regulatory filings and certain other conditions precedent. First drawdown of the debt facility is expected in first quarter 2025, which is in line with the company's financing plan to keep the project on track for a first pour in fourth quarter 2025.
Key terms of the debt facility include:
Senior secured debt facility of up to $105-million (U.S.), with the ability to increase it to up to $130-million (U.S.);
Repayment moratorium of more than two years and final maturity in March, 2030;
Interest rate of 6.50 per cent per annum over a secured overnight financing rate reference rate, with 50 per cent of interest capitalized during the construction period;
No commitment fee payable;
Original issue discount of 2.00 per cent of the debt facility paid pro rata upon the financing of each tranche;
An additional interest payment based on a gold price participation formula currently equivalent to approximately $300 per ounce vis-a-vis the current consensus gold price forecast, applicable on 3,600 oz of gold per quarter for 15 quarters (to be increased pro rata if the debt facility is increased to $130-million (U.S.)), with the ability to prepay on early repayment of the debt facility;
Partner alignment compensation equal to 1.00 per cent of the debt facility payable in Robex common shares on the closing date;
No mandatory gold hedging or royalties;
No additional cost overrun financing or cash sweep requirements.
Robex managing director Matthew Wilcox said: "We are pleased to welcome Sprott Resource Lending as our financing partner, who have completed comprehensive due diligence on the Kiniero gold project before securing investment committee approval for the same, and look forward to closing the facility to achieve first drawdown in Q1 2025. This debt facility will allow us to keep our target of Q4 2025 for first pour."
We seek Safe Harbor.
